-- Indonesian Equity Movers: Energi Mega Persada, Jasa Marga
-- B y   G r e g   A h l s t r a n d   a n d   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2012-06-11T09:10:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/energi-mega-jasa-marga-medco-energi-indonesian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close of trading.  The  Jakarta Composite Index (JCI)  rose 1.1 percent to 3,866.21,
the first gain in three days and the highest close since May 30.  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG)  , Indonesia’s second-
largest listed oil company, increased 5.8 percent to 145 rupiah,
snapping a two-day loss. Crude oil for July delivery increased
2.4 percent to $86.13 a barrel in  New York . Futures rose 1.1
percent last week, the first weekly gain in six.  PT Jasa Marga (JSMR)  , Indonesia’s largest toll-road
operator, gained 2 percent to 5,150 rupiah, the sharpest advance
this month. The company plans to build four toll roads on
Sumatra island, Bisnis Indonesia reported today, citing
President Director Adityawarman.  To contact the reporters on this story:
